Trying to find little moments to draw more often✨

Goodbye to the best house. I used to sneak out of the upstair window and climb down the side of the chimney to go hangout at the beach with my friends. We threw countless bonfires and parties in the backyard. Our neighborhood was exceptional. Growing up we would get together weekly for “Friday Night Dinner Club” for a potluck with all the kids and parents. My parents supported my love of art by letting me paint murals anywhere I wanted to. What a wonderful place to grow up. I hope the new owners make as many happy memories here as we did.🤍🤍🤍

You Nerds wanted to see more “serious” art well here ya go! This is a sketch I’ve been working on for a while. About a year ago I was feeling pretty lost. I didn’t recognize myself as the thriving, happy person I had been before the pandemic. Don’t get me wrong, I was happy but lost just the same. Maybe some of you can relate to this feeling?
•
You can never return to the person you once were but you can mourn her and grow from their ashes into something else that’s stronger and also beautiful.
•

“Nothing is completely original” - @austinkleon 
•
A look behind the curtain of my drawing process. I get intimidated by all of the amazing artists that are on social media all the time. How do they come up with such amazing ideas, composition, color, palettes, etc. ?? It can be discouraging to even start a drawing when other people are already doing it so much better than you, but I have come to learn that all artists use references of some kind. I used to think that it was cheating or  bad form, but actually, it is the creative way. I highly suggest you read the book, Steal like an Artist by @austinkleon if this is something that you are relating to👌🏻🖤.

•
Let’s talk about the amount of time spent gathering inspiration and reference imagery for our art projects. I probably spend half of the amount of hours it takes me to complete any project researching. Occasionally inspiration will strike out of nowhere and when that happens, it’s the best feeling ever! But… It rarely ever happens like that, at least for me. 🤣🥲 Pinterest and my Barnes & Noble membership subscription have me in a chokehold because of how much I rely on them for my creative ideas. I think sometimes we can put too much pressure on ourselves to be “original”. I say be thoughtful and be intentional.

Happy Halloween Nerds🧛🏼‍♀️❤️🍾🎃✨👻🦇 WE MADE IT!!! Wishing you all happy memories today and unpleasant dreams tonight (ifykyk). Thank you to all the fellow Halloween lovers who have followed my art this year! I never thought I’d gain so much support so quickly🖤🖤🖤. More spooky art to come through the end of the year even though I am also a fan of Christmas😂👌🏻.
